svg.title: Map titled “The Battle of Battle 1st Position. About 7:30.” A railway is drawn and labeled horizontally at the top. A road crosses the railway, labeled “level crossing,” and turns southwest. An “Inn: with the King of Kent and his Staff” is marked along the road. Military formations are drawn, labeled “Men of Kent” and “Men of Sussex.” The “Men of Sussex” are at the south of the map, on top of a hill marked with elevation lines, and the “Men of Kent” are north below the hill, in front of the road and railway.
